.main` in Native Image since that might affect access to declared methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Method Invocation in Testing**\\n\\nI’m considering whether `Method.invoke` might be blocked unless it's marked as invokable. If it throws an `UnsupportedFeature`, that could mean coverage isn't recorded due to a missing reflect-config. The goal here is improving test coverage, not focusing on the metadata.\\n\\nIf the test runs with a Forge metadata generator, the agent should ideally register the invoke. However, it seems the agent didn’t detect the `Method.invoke`. Maybe it's due to catching the `VersionMessagePrintedException` before reaching that point. I need to confirm if the line number mismatch is affecting the execution. If so, I wonder how to ensure the call is effectively visible to the agent.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Method Invocation Success**\\n\\nI'm pondering how if `Method.invoke` throws an exception before returning, that might not be logged as successful dynamic access. Ideally, I'd want the target to return successfully. Since I can't modify the library directly, I wonder if providing an alternative `Driver` class would work.\\n\\nIt looks like `XJCFacade` loads its classes via its defining classloader, so maybe classpath ordering in tests is causing the test classes to take precedence. But could the class name `com.sun.tools.xjc.Driver` be shadowing the library version? That's something to investigate further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing challenges**\\n\\nI’m grappling with the idea that I can't place tests within library packages since the rules clearly say to keep tests outside. The conflict arises, as the `XJCFacade.class` is loaded by the system classloader, which makes it tricky to create a custom classloader unless I use a child-first approach with a separate instance of `XJCFacade`. Yet, if the dynamic class loading isn’t supported here, I'm unsure how to handle methods requiring reflection since that’s restricted unless necessary for public API.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reassessing class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm facing quite the challenge with class loading for tests. The pattern isn't ideal, but I could simplify things by creating a test class named `com.sun.tools.xjc.Driver` under the test source. However, placing tests in the same package as the library isn’t allowed. I wonder if using a Java agent instrumentation makes sense, but PowerMock doesn’t seem viable either. Maybe running `XJCFacade.main` in a separate process could work, though it complicates coverage. Plus, trying to utilize `SecurityManager` adds its own set of issues, especially with `System.exit`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring method invocation issues**\\n\\nI'm trying to unpack why the call to `Method.invoke` might not be recording properly. I thought that maybe it didn’t capture an exception because it occurred before `Driver.main`, but that doesn’t seem to be the case. With the `SecurityManager` and a standard `PrintStream`, there’s no exception until `System.exit`, yet `Method.invoke` still throws at the target. I wonder if the instrumentation for `Method.invoke` logs only after control returns from the native reflection call, which could explain the discrepancy. Why isn't it consistent in this scenario?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Native Image support**\\n\\nI'm considering that the system property at runtime might not be beneficial for Native Image, and it seems like SecurityManager might not be supported. I don’t want to rely solely on that. If PrintStream gets involved, it appears I wouldn't need a security manager at all. It's a bit confusing, and I want to ensure I'm getting this right! Let's see how I can work around these limitations effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sTt5PYQ9Be1rbcOd7R84EA1N|fc_0b18d20b683614f20169fe407a76bc81a3bcdc156a74c264c0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-xjc/4.0.6/main/extracted/com/sun/tools/xjc/util/Util.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1457, "output": 2543, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44960, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778270289665, "responseId": "resp_0b18d20b683614f20169fe40534fac81a39a70e16c77b9089e"}}
