tential null cases and consider class visibility, especially if I'm using reflection. If the test class is nested and private, there's a question of method access. I’m not sure if `Method.invoke` can work with a private class — I'd need the class to be accessible to avoid an `IllegalAccessException`. The visibility and access are key here, along with any necessary imports.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Contemplating class resources**\\n\\nI'm considering whether we should depend on native images, especially since they often don't include .class resources without the `-H:+AllowIncompleteClasspath` option. It seems like I could catch `Throwable` and check if it includes an unsupported error. If it does, I guess I would return to avoid issues; otherwise, I'd just throw the error. I really want to avoid skipping anything important here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_00rkVKF85B42InwsaFa1ukPN|fc_0b18d20b683614f20169fe418e4bac81a3a1e3020380401211", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-xjc/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_xjc/XJCFacadeTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.security.Permission;\n", "newText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.security.Permission;\n"}, {"oldText": "import com.sun.tools.xjc.XJCFacade;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n", "newText": "import com.sun.tools.xjc.XJCFacade;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    private static boolean installSecurityManagerIfSupported(SecurityManager securityManager) {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void mainInvokeReturnsWhenLoadedDriverMainReturns() throws Exception {\n        ReturningDriver.lastArgs = null;\n        try {\n            ClassLoader loader = new XjcFacadeIsolatingClassLoader(XJCFacade.class.getClassLoader());\n            Class<?> facadeClass = loader.loadClass(\"com.sun.tools.xjc.XJCFacade\");\n            Method main = facadeClass.getMethod(\"main\", String[].class);\n\n            main.invoke(null, (Object) new String[] {\"-source\", \"3.0\"});\n\n            assertThat(ReturningDriver.lastArgs).containsExactly(\"-source\", \"3.0\");\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n            if (cause instanceof Error error) {\n                rethrowIfNotNativeImageDynamicClassLoadingError(error);\n                return;\n            }\n            throw exception;\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowIfNotNativeImageDynamicClassLoadingError(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    private static boolean installSecurityManagerIfSupported(SecurityManager securityManager) {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class VersionMessagePrintStream extends PrintStream {\n", "newText": "    private static void rethrowIfNotNativeImageDynamicClassLoadingError(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class ReturningDriver {\n        private static String[] lastArgs;\n\n        private ReturningDriver() {\n        }\n\n        public static void main(String[] args) {\n            lastArgs = args.clone();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class XjcFacadeIsolatingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final String DRIVER_CLASS_NAME = \"com.sun.tools.xjc.Driver\";\n        private static final String FACADE_CLASS_NAME = \"com.sun.tools.xjc.XJCFacade\";\n        private static final String SECURE_LOADER_CLA